(secondQuint)A Case Management Intervention to Prevent ER Visits in HIV-infected Persons.

 One year retrospective look at outcome measures followed by a one year trial of a phone call after each ER visit in half of the group.

 Outcomes measured are cost, ER visits, hospitalizations, death, length of stay.

 Adults only, English or Spanish, questionnaire on depression, appointments, drug use with referral to case management services, drug rehab services, or followup appointments.

 Time for intervention is recorded to estimate cost.

